.TH "collapse_pte_mapped_thp" 9 "collapse_pte_mapped_thp" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
collapse_pte_mapped_thp \- Try to collapse a pte-mapped THP for mm at address haddr.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" collapse_pte_mapped_thp
.BI "(struct mm_struct *mm "  ","
.BI "unsigned long addr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mm" 12
process address space where collapse happens
.IP "addr" 12
THP collapse address
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function checks whether all the PTEs in the PMD are pointing to the
right THP. If so, retract the page table so the THP can refault in with
as pmd-mapped.
